[SN]TITLE[SN]
Eleven youths charged over Edinburgh assaults

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Eleven youths have been charged after three people were assaulted in the Gorgie area of Edinburgh last month.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police said three males, all aged 17, suffered serious facial injuries in an incident near Robertson Avenue at about 21:00 on Wednesday 12 April.
Eleven teenagers, aged between 14 and 17 have been charged with various assault offences.
A 15-year-old boy has also been charged with robbery and a 17-year-old with possession of a bladed item.
They will all be reported to the children's reporter and procurator fiscal.
